<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000060#     2#          506#">Va. Code Ann. § 60.2-506</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_60.2-506"/><heading><desig>§ 60.2-506.</desig><title>Financing of benefits to state employees</title></heading><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_a"/><heading><desig>A.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> The Commonwealth of Virginia shall have the option to:</p></bodyText><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_a_1"/><heading><desig>1.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Treat all of its branches of government and all of its instrumentalities as one employer;</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_a_2"/><heading><desig>2.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Treat each branch of government, judicial, executive, and legislative, as an individual employer; or</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_a_3"/><heading><desig>3.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Treat each of its instrumentalities as an individual employer.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_a_4"/><heading><desig>4.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> The option described herein shall be exercised by the Governor.</p></bodyText></level></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_b"/><heading><desig>B.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> If the option contained in subdivision 1 of subsection A of this section is exercised, the Commonwealth may elect to finance benefits to its employees by either taxes, as set forth in <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 60.2-526"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 60.2-526">§§ 60.2-526<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000060#     2#          526#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> through <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 60.2-533"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 60.2-533">60.2-533<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000060#     2#          533#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, or payments in lieu of taxes.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_c"/><heading><desig>C.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> If the option contained in either subdivision 2 or 3 of subsection A of this section is exercised, each such individual employer may elect to finance benefits to its employees by either taxes, as set forth in <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 60.2-526"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 60.2-526">§§ 60.2-526<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000060#     2#          526#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> through <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 60.2-533"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 60.2-533">60.2-533<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000060#     2#          533#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, or payments in lieu of taxes.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_d"/><heading><desig>D.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> If the election to make payments in lieu of taxes is exercised, payments shall be made into the fund in an amount equivalent to the amount of regular and extended benefits paid that is attributable to service in the employ of the Commonwealth. If benefits paid to an individual are based on wages paid by more than one employer and one or more employers are liable for payments in lieu of taxes, the amount payable to the fund by each employer that is liable for such payments shall be determined in accordance with the provisions of <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 60.2-504"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 60.2-504">§ 60.2-504<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000060#     2#          504#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_e"/><heading><desig>E.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Payments made in lieu of taxes by the Commonwealth into the Unemployment Trust Fund shall be made at such times and in such manner as the Commission may determine and prescribe.</p></bodyText></level><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p>1971, Ex. Sess., c. 235, § 60.1-89.1; 1977, c. 330; 1979, c. 634; 1986, c. 480.</p></bodyText></historyItem></historyGroup></history></level></statute></legislativeDocBody><metadata><dc:metadata xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><dc:identifier identifierScheme="PGUID">urn:contentItem:5K0Y-PTM0-004G-K0P7-00000-00</dc:identifier><dc:source sourceScheme="productContentSetIdentifier">10816</dc:source><dc:date dateType="last-updated">2016-06-15</dc:date></dc:metadata><publicationInfo><publicationName>CODE OF VIRGINIA </publicationName><copyright>Copyright © 2016  by Matthew Bender &amp; Company, Inc. a member of the LexisNexis Group. All rights reserved</copyright></publicationInfo><hierarchy><hierarchyLevel levelType="title"><heading><desig>TITLE 60.2.</desig><title>UNEMPLOYMENT COMPENSATION</title></heading><hierarchyLevel levelType="chapter"><heading><desig>CHAPTER 5.</desig><title>TAXATION</title></heading><hierarchyLevel levelType="article"><heading><desig>ARTICLE 1.</desig><title>EMPLOYER TAXATION</title></heading></hierarchyLevel></hierarchyLevel></hierarchyLevel></hierarchy><classification classificationScheme="legal"><classificationItem><className>Governments</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6MjdEQjE4OUJDMzQxNDNEMEI0RTI1QUFCMzJENjEwRTA7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD0</classCode><classificationItem><className>Employees &amp; Officials</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6OTU3RThFMjRDRjdGNDRFNTg0NEYyMUM1NEU3MzdCQTU7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6QURCRDNBRjBGRTE0NEFBRUEzNUU1MzFGQjg3MTM4MDI</classCode></classificationItem></classificationItem><classificationItem><className>Tax Law</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6OTNEM0E2OEE0RkQyNEY1MDhBQzdGMkQ4ODI4QTJDODE7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD0</classCode><classificationItem><className>General Overview</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6MTdCMzZBOUNFNjAwNEZFM0E0NEU3ODJFM0EyRDMyNEI7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6RUYwREVBQ0NGQ0UxNDY2REE0MzMzMDE5RDRGNTEyNjg</classCode></classificationItem><classificationItem><className>General Overview</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6QTg1NEI3MzExQjg0NERDMUFCQjMxNEM5QURBMkM4Rjk7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6NDRDOUUwNjUzMUE1NEI4RDk4ODE3NUZFM0VCQzEwM0Q</classCode></classificationItem><classificationItem><className>General Overview</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6NDc0NDFERUNFQUY5NDA0MUFBOUQyOEM1Mzc3MzQxNDg7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6NUU3MDZDQzRFRDA4NDFCNEFFNjI1MDc1QzZGODkzMDE</classCode></classificationItem></classificationItem></classification></metadata></legislativeDoc>